{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:08:36.398742", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted solution:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): load_balancer\n- Root cause(s): arp_acl_block\n\nRationale summary:\n- The load balancer (10.200.0.7) cannot resolve ARP for web_server_0..3 (10.200.0.3/4/5/6), with ip neigh showing FAILED/INCOMPLETE and ICMP returning Destination Host Unreachable. \n- Other nodes (server_access_router, hosts) can reach these servers and have correct ARP/MAC entries; LB can ARP to router, DNS, and DHCP on the same VLAN.\n- This points to selective ARP suppression/filtering on the LB’s eth0 rather than a broadcast-domain or routing issue, consistent with an ARP ACL/block on the LB.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2744, "output_tokens": 170, "total_tokens": 2914, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
